==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perchromic
<hw>Per*chro"mic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>per-</ets> + <ets>chromic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a certain one of the highly oxidized
compounds of chromium, which has a deep blue color, and is produced by
the action of hydrogen peroxide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perciform</ent>⟦br⟧
